      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can picture it as an emergency mobilization where the immature neutrophils are quickly pushed out by the bone marrow. These neutrophils then execute a targeted attack on the bacteria through several mechanisms. They first perform **phagocytosis**, engulfing the pathogens, and then they deploy lethal substances like reactive oxygen species (the 'respiratory burst') and antimicrobial enzymes stored within their granules to destroy the ingested bacteria.",
